 that inspired Hume the most, from his family estate near the Scottish border to Paris, where, as an older man, he was warmly embraced by French society. Baggini shows how Hume put his philosophy into practice in a life that blended reason and passion, study and leisure, and relaxation and enjoyment.The Great Guide includes 145 Humean maxims for living well, on topics ranging from the meaning of success and the value of travel to friendship, facing death, identity, and the importance of leisure. This book shows how life is far richer with Hume as your guide.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aHumanity. 0aWell-being. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  a7 Habits of Highly Effective People.  aA Treatise of Human Nature.  aEdinburgh.  aFrance.  aFrancis Bacon.  aGeorge Berkeley.  aJohn Locke.  aLa Flèche.  aNewtonianism.  aNinewells.  aNorman Vincent Peale.  aParis salons.  aPower of Positive Thinking.  aRousseau.  aScottish Enlightenment.  aStephen R. Covey.  aThomas Hobbes.  aaesthetics.  aepistemology.  aethics.  ahow to live.  alifestyle changes.  ametaphysics.  anaturalism.  anaturalistic science of man.  aphilosophical empiricism.  asalon.  aself-help.  aself-improvement books.  askepticism.  astoicism.  atravel writing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021 Englishz978311075415508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021z9783110753929oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073